<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>UpdateScoreCommand</computeroutput>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Command that carries score update information to the ScorePoolManager  </para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_326351fd6fbd1ed4d80f0b2b180f7c49_1autotoc_md279">
<title>Usage</title><para>Commands are typically issued by scoring systems (e.g., <computeroutput>CombatScoringSystem</computeroutput>) when a scoring event occurs:</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".cpp"><codeline><highlight class="keyword">auto</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>scoreContext<sp/>=<sp/>types::ScoreValueContext{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.scoreTypeId<sp/>=<sp/>ScoreTypeId::id&lt;KillReward&gt;(),</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.scorePoolId<sp/>=<sp/>playerScorePoolId,</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>.value<sp/>=<sp/>100.0</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">};</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">updateContext.commandBuffer().add&lt;UpdateScoreCommand&gt;(std::move(scoreValueContext));</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
